<DATELINE>
   SINGAPORE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Singapore Airport Terminal Services (Sats) is teaming up with Vietnamese
groups in a USDollars 15m venture to provide cargo handling services at Ho
Chi Minh City airport, in the south of Vietnam.
Sats, a subsidiary of Singapore Airlines (SIA), will hold a 30 per cent
stake in the venture, with the rest controlled by Vietnam Airlines and a
local Vietnamese company.
