<HEADLINE>
FT  31 AUG 94 / International Company News: Progress at Howard Smith
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Howard Smith, the Australian industrial group, yesterday announced a
ADollars 56.8m (Dollars 41m) profit after tax and abnormals in the year to
end-June, up from ADollars 47m a year ago. The rise was scored on revenues
of ADollars 89.2m, 17.5 per cent higher than in the previous year.
The company, which acquired the large BBC Hardware retail chain in July,
said it was adding the Campbells Hardware Group for ADollars 81m from
Jamison Equity, the Australian conglomerate.
The company is also pulling out of the stevedoring business. It is planning
to sell its 25 per cent interest in Australian Stevedores for ADollars 28m
to Jamison Equity unless ANL, the government-owned shipping business,
exercises a pre-emptive right.
</TEXT>
