FT  31 AUG 94 / Sri Lankan peace move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MERVYN DE SILVA
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COLOMBO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mrs Chandrika Kumaratunge, the new Sri Lankan prime minister, will meet the
army chief and other service commanders tomorrow to discuss a ceasefire in
the 11-year long war against the separatist 'Tamil Tigers', Mervyn de Silva
reports from Colombo. They will also discuss a partial lifting of the
economic embargo imposed on the northern peninsula of Jaffna, by the
previous United National party government regime. The UNP was defeated by
Mrs Kumaratunge's People's Alliance, a left-inclined coalition in
parliamentary elections on August 16.
