FT  31 AUG 94 / International Company News: Royal Oak out of Lac running
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   VANCOUVER
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Royal Oak Mines, the Canadian gold producer, has withdrawn its offer for
rival Lac Minerals, Reuter reports from Vancouver.
Royal Oak started the bidding war for Lac on July 7 with a hostile takeover
offer, subsequently increasing its bid to CDollars 5 and two of its shares
for each Lac share. However, American Barrick, another Canadian gold
producer, last week secured the support of the Lac board for its offer of
CDollars 5 and 0.325 of its shares for each Lac share.
Royal Oak will tender its 3.78m Lac shares, acquired before Royal Oak
launched its bid, to the American Barrick offer.
