<HEADLINE>
FT  31 AUG 94 / International Company News: Bank of Nova Scotia ahead in
third quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bank of Nova Scotia, Canada's fourth-biggest bank, lifted third-quarter net
profit to CDollars 198m (USDollars 141m), or 80 cents a share, up 8.2 per
cent from CDollars 183m, or 77 cents, a year earlier.
Return on equity was 13.91 per cent, against 14.39 per cent. However, the
bank recorded a 12.6 per cent rise in net interest income, due to strong
growth in commercial and mortgage lending and better overseas markets.
Other income was up 20.4 per cent, though expenses rose 18.5 per cent due to
the absorption of Montreal Trust, the Canadian trust company.
Annual provision for credit losses was CDollars 567m at July 31, unchanged
from the previous quarter.
Net profit for the nine-month period was CDollars 277m, or 95 cents, down
from CDollars 520m, or CDollars 2.18, a year earlier.
The 1994 period included CDollars 305m special charges taken in the second
quarter following the acquisition of Montreal Trust.
Excluding these, net profit was CDollars 582m, up 12 per cent.
</TEXT>
