FT  31 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Cathay Intl ahead to Pounds 469,000
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cathay International Holdings, the London quoted investment company formerly
known as Stonehill, yesterday announced that net assets had risen from
Pounds 62.9m to Pounds 233.2m, following a series of investments in China
made last year.
Pre-tax profits for the year to March amounted to Pounds 469,000 (Pounds
264,000), however, the company received no meaningful contribution from
either of two substantial new assets, the Landmark Hotel in Shenzhen and the
Xiyuan Hotel in Beijing.
Last year, the company was transformed from a shell, containing the
Stonehill business park, into the holding company for those two hotels and a
related property development project.
Turnover during the year rose from Pounds 4.03m to Pounds 5.94m, and
operating profit amounted to Pounds 1.28m (Pounds 1.86m).
Losses per share emerged at 0.09p (0.066p). There is no dividend.
The company has eliminated the deficit on its profit and loss account, but
still owes Pounds 336,000 of preference share dividends. It has given no
timescale for reviving dividends.
