FT  31 AUG 94 / BSkyB adds Pounds 3 a month to prices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Subscribers to British Sky Broadcasting services will have to pay Pounds 3 a
month more from the beginning of October.
The company began informing its subscribers at the weekend of the price
rise, which looks designed to increase the rate of payback of the more than
Pounds 1.75bn invested in the satellite television venture.
The rise is being added to all four tiers of subscriptions so that the basic
multi-channel package will in future cost Pounds 9.99. Multi-channel plus
one premium service, such as the Sports Channel or a film channel, will cost
Pounds 14.99, multi-channel plus two premium channels Pounds 19.99 and the
entire package Pounds 22.99.
BSkyB, in which Pearson, owner of the Financial Times, has a significant
stake, had 3.45m subscribers at the end of June. If they all continue to
subscribe then the gross additional revenue over a year would be about
Pounds 125m.
