analysed the number of jobs created in 34 towns and cities in England and
Wales between 1985 and 1992. It says there is no relationship between job
opportunities in these areas and their distance from trunk roads.
Doncaster, less than 20 minutes from the M1 motorway, experienced a fraction
of the rise in job opportunities of Grimsby, 70 minutes from the M1, the
report says.
