FT  31 AUG 94 / Italy delays pension fraud move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italian cabinet ministers met yesterday to discuss cutting pension spending
but delayed any decision on an amnesty for disability fraud. Implementing
savings on pensions is a key part of prime minister Silvio Berlusconi's plan
to cut the budget deficit. The government suspects that as many as 3m people
in a country of 57m receive some monthly payments for disabilities they do
not have. Cabinet secretary Gianni Letta said the ministers agreed to
overhaul the entire disability system. But he told reporters that an amnesty
for disability fraudsters, which had been proposed by some coalition
partners, had not yet been taken up for discussion.
