FT  30 AUG 94 / More InterCity trains set to break strike today
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Rail plans to operate services from most major cities to London in
spite of industrial action by signalmen from noon today until noon on
Thursday.
In all cases, passengers should check the hours of operation locally.
Services may be subject to alteration at short notice. Routes expected to
have services during the strike tomorrow afternoon, throughout Wednesday and
on Thursday morning are:
InterCity Anglia: Liverpool Street - Ipswich, Norwich; Ipswich - Felixtowe;
Ipswich - Lowestoft; Chiltern Lines: Normal service London Marylebone -
Banbury; Gatwick Express; Network SouthCentral: London Victoria to Beckenham
Jn, Three Bridges, Leatherhead and West Croydon via Mitcham Junction; London
Bridge to Wimbledon, Sutton, Caterham and Smitham; no services to Brighton;
Great Eastern: London Liverpool St - Shenfield, Southend; Liverpool St -
Ipswich; Wickford - Southminster; Marks Tey - Sudbury; Isle of Wight: normal
service; London, Tilbury, Southend: London Liverpool St - Shoeburyness;
Stanford-le-Hope - Pitsea; Upminster - Grays; North London Railways: London
Euston - Northampton, Birmingham; Watford Jn - Kilburn High Road (for
Underground); Watford Jn - St Albans; South Eastern: London
Victoria/Blackfriars - Faversham; Victoria - Orpington; Victoria - Ashford;
Charing Cross - Ashford; Blackfriars - Sevenoaks; Charing Cross - Orpington;
Cannon St - Hayes; Tonbridge - Tunbridge Wells; Sittingbourne - Sheerness;
Ashford - Folkestone Central; Cannon St - Eltham, Dartford, Gravesend; South
West Trains: London Waterloo - Wimbledon, Epsom, Hampton Court, Woking,
Guildford via Cobham; Waterloo - Basingstoke, Salisbury; Thames Trains:
London Paddington - Reading, Oxford, Banbury; Slough - Windsor; Maidenhead -
Marlow; Twyford - Henley; Reading - Newbury; Reading - Basingstoke; Oxford -
Bicester; Oxford - Gt Malvern; Thameslink: Moorgate - St Albans, Bedford;
West Anglia Great Northern: London Kings Cross - Peterborough; Kings Cross -
Royston, Hertford North; Liverpool Street - Stansted Airport, Cambridge;
Cardiff Valleys: Penarth - Caerphilly; Coryton - Bute Road; also replacement
bus services; Regional Railways Central: Birmingham - Leicester,
Peterborough; Nottingham - Chesterfield, Sheffield; Nottingham - Birmingham,
Gloucester, Newstead, Derby; Matlock - Derby; Peterborough - Spalding;
Loughborough - Leicester; InterCity Cross Country: Manchester - Edinburgh;
Bristol - Derby; Birmingham - Manchester; InterCity East Coast: London Kings
Cross - Leeds, Edinburgh; InterCity Great Western: Paddington - Bristol,
Plymouth; Paddington - Cardiff, Swansea; Paddington - Cheltenham, Worcester;
InterCity Midland: London St Pancras - Sheffield, Nottingham; Reg Rlys NE:
York - Berwick; York - Bradford, Hebden Bridge; Hull - Bridlington; Leeds -
Doncaster, Ilkley, Shipley, Manchester Piccadilly; Bradford - Ilkley;
Doncaster - Sheffield, Scunthorpe; Newcastle - MetroCentre; Middlesbrough -
Manchester Airport. Some replacement buses; Reg Rlys NW: Manchester -
Bolton, Preston, Lancaster; Manchester - Stockport, Alderley Edge;
Manchester - New Mills, Hadfield/Glossop, Leeds, Manchester Airport,
Barrow-in-Furness; Manchester Airport - Middlesbrough; Oxenholme -
Windermere; Llandudno Junction - Blaenau Ffestiniog. Also some bus services;
ScotRail: Edinburgh - Glasgow, Fife, North Berwick, Bathgate; Glasgow - Ayr,
Kilmarnock, East Kilbride, Motherwell, Greenock, Wemyss Bay, Paisley, Largs,
Stranraer; Inverness - Wick/Thurso, Kyle of Lochalsh; Fort William -
Mallaig; Reg Rlys S Wales &amp; West: Swansea - Llanelli, Cardiff, Bristol;
Birmingham - Exeter; Bristol - Salisbury; Gloucester - Swindon; Exeter -
Paignton, Plymouth, Barnstaple; Plymouth - Gunnislake; St Erth - St Ives;
MerseyRail: Liverpool - Southport, Kirkby, Ormskirk; InterCity West Coast:
Euston - Manchester, Glasgow; Euston - Wolverhampton.
