<HEADLINE>
FT  30 AUG 94 / PIA has applications of 4,000 financial advisers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Personal Investment Authority, the watchdog to protect the private
investor, will today publish figures likely to show that applications from
companies and individuals regulated by Lautro and Fimbra have reached 4,000
out of a potential membership of about 5,500, Alison Smith writes.
There is less than five weeks to the deadline by which any financial adviser
must apply to the PIA for authorisation to remain in retail financial
services. The regulator became operational last month.
The gap between the actual and potential numbers of applicants has sparked
suggestions that there could be a significant fall in the independent
financial advice sector, as many now authorised decide not to continue under
the PIA.
</TEXT>
