<HEADLINE>
FT  30 AUG 94 / Adverts promote fish consumption
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A Pounds 1m television advertising campaign to promote consumption of fish
is being launched this week.
The five-week campaign is being run by the Sea Fish Industry Authority, a
promotional body funded by levies on fish landings and imports. The
authority said the campaign was the first on television since 1988 and aimed
to recoup 'two lost years' when it was unable to advertise because of a cut
in the levy.
Cod, haddock and plaice account for about half of UK fish consumption
although 60 varieties of fish and shellfish are available. The authority
said, however, that the campaign was not 'geared towards encouraging people
to experiment with fish'.
</TEXT>
